edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device
Class PrimitiveSite

java.lang.Object
  edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device.PrimitiveSite
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class PrimitiveSite
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class represents the primitive sites found in XDLRC files. Theses represent places on the FPGA where a particular instance of a primitive (or XDL 'inst') can reside.

Author:
Chris Lavin

isCompatiblePrimitiveType

public boolean isCompatiblePrimitiveType(PrimitiveType otherType)
This method will check if the PrimitiveType otherType can be placed at this primitive site. Most often only if they are equal can this be true. However there are a few special cases that require extra handling. For example a SLICEL can reside in a SLICEM site but not vice versa.

Parameters:
otherType - The primitive type to try to place on this site.
Returns:
True if otherType can be placed at this primitive site, false otherwise.

Parameters:

Returns:
